      Knowledge result

      Sydney Opera House
      Performing arts centre in the City of Sydney, New South Wales

      Description

      The Sydney Opera House is a multi-venue performing arts centre at Sydney Harbour in Sydney, New South Wales, Australia. It is one of the 20th century's most famous and distinctive buildings. Wikipedia
      Construction started: 2 March 1959
      Architecture firm: Arup Group
      Founded: 1973
      Architect: Jørn Utzon
      Did you know: Paul Robeson was the first to perform in the Opera House. nationalgeographic.com.au
